Happy 2023, my friends! 🥂🤍

For those that are new here and those who are not, I wanted to give a quick hello. For those that have followed my career and journey as a wedding and event planner since 2010, thank you from the bottom of my heart. For those that are new, I also cannot thank you enough for being willing to check out the prettiness that I get to curate. As a small business, I started CRW in the recession, survived the pandemic, and the craziness that was post pandemic…now we’re in another recession and yet, I am grateful for stability because of YOUR bookings. 🤍 Thank you to all the couples who have put their faith in me and my team to curate and execute your events. None of this journey is lost on me and I am grateful for what is to come for 2023. I am still booking for this year and beyond so please share this profile with anyone feeling overwhelmed / in need of a planner. Destinations, private estates, hotels, venues. I do them all! Cheers to another beautiful year ahead! 🤍

Come plan a wedding with me Puerto Escondido, Mexico! Part i - the welcome night! 🇲🇽🏝️🤍

Complete with guests in all white! Mariachi! Mezcalitas! Grill on the beach! And as much dancing as your calves can stand! 🏝️ 

Stay tuned for part ✌🏼- the wedding day! 

#destinatonwedding #destinationweddingplanner #mexicowedding #loveislove

And this began my Mexico destination wedding portfolio. Cece and Sam were the coolest and funniest clients where they had 100(🫠) of their nearest and dearest fly to Puerto Escondido to celebrate with them (GOALS!!) 

When people find out my job, I often hear: “there’s no such thing as a flawless event” and you can immediately hear my response: “you haven’t been to mine.” And I deeply mean it. This weekend was PERFECT from beginning to end albeit the language barriers and new country dynamics, it was simply *chefs kiss* 🤍🤌🏼 I’ll remember this one for as long as I live. Cheers to Cece and Sam. And Cheers to more destinations like this one (I have a few down the pipe - standby!)

Getting married in Mexico like… 🤌🏼

Backyard events are my speciality. 🏠

But don’t be fooled, it’s not cheaper to have a backyard wedding because more often than not, the rentals, toilets, parking permits, and generators offset the cost of doing it to “save money on a venue.” Anything is doable of course which is why doing backyards and estates are some of my most favorite venues because I get to dream up a whole new and unique experience to my couples. It gives such a beautiful personal touch and it gives me big Father of The Bride energy which has been a favorite movie of mine since it came out. 🤍
